00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:02.300
- Welcome to the Huberman Lab Podcast,

00:00:02.300 --> 00:00:03.417
where we discuss science

00:00:03.417 --> 00:00:05.953
and science-based tools for everyday life.

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:12.050
I'm Andrew Huberman, and I'm
a Professor of Neurobiology

00:00:12.050 --> 00:00:15.310
and Ophthalmology at
Stanford School of Medicine.

00:00:15.310 --> 00:00:18.270
Today, we are discussing
the immune system,

00:00:18.270 --> 00:00:20.640
and we are also discussing
the nervous system,

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:22.170
which is the brain, spinal cord,

00:00:22.170 --> 00:00:24.010
and the connections of
the brain and spinal cord

00:00:24.010 --> 00:00:25.763
with all the organs of the body.

00:00:26.690 --> 00:00:29.620
We are also going to discuss
how the nervous system can be

00:00:29.620 --> 00:00:33.720
used to activate and
control the immune system.

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:35.960
Now, about 10, 20 years ago,

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:38.760
if somebody said that
the mind could control

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:41.300
the immune system, they'd
probably get laughed out

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:42.960
of most academic conferences.

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:44.570
And certainly the work
wouldn't be published

00:00:44.570 --> 00:00:48.060
in quality journals, but
nowadays there are dozens,

00:00:48.060 --> 00:00:51.550
if not hundreds of quality
peer-reviewed studies

00:00:51.550 --> 00:00:54.700
on how the mind and how the nervous system

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:58.230
can control activation
of the immune system.

00:00:58.230 --> 00:01:00.860
This is a wonderful
growing body of research.

00:01:00.860 --> 00:01:02.510
And just to give you a hint of

00:01:02.510 --> 00:01:05.790
where we are headed with
this, just this last week,

00:01:05.790 --> 00:01:07.950
there was a paper published in "Nature"

00:01:07.950 --> 00:01:11.070
which is the apex journal
for scientific publishing,

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:13.763
premiere journal, extremely stringent,

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:16.200
a paper published in "Nature"

00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:19.240
from Qiufu Ma's lab at
Harvard Medical School,

00:01:19.240 --> 00:01:22.700
explored how acupuncture can reduce

00:01:22.700 --> 00:01:24.620
inflammation in the body.

00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:28.110
And I will describe this study
in a bit more detail later,

00:01:28.110 --> 00:01:32.700
but what they discovered was
that by stimulating the body

00:01:32.700 --> 00:01:36.480
in particular ways at
particular sites on the body,

00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:41.040
they were able to liberate
certain cells and molecules

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:43.960
that enhance the function
of the immune system,

00:01:43.960 --> 00:01:45.760
and potentially can be used to combat

00:01:45.760 --> 00:01:47.580
different types of infection.

00:01:47.580 --> 00:01:49.650
And just to give you another little hint,

00:01:49.650 --> 00:01:53.310
they found that a particular
type of organ tissue

00:01:53.310 --> 00:01:55.620
called fascia, some of you
may have heard of fascia,

00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:57.980
fascia surrounds our muscles.

00:01:57.980 --> 00:01:58.813
Just to look at it,

00:01:58.813 --> 00:02:00.380
you might think it's a
kind of useless tissue,

00:02:00.380 --> 00:02:02.130
it's sort of like a dense bag

00:02:02.130 --> 00:02:04.030
in which the muscles are contained.

00:02:04.030 --> 00:02:06.140
Well, it turns out that those dense bags

00:02:06.140 --> 00:02:07.450
are much smarter than we thought.

00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:08.620
They don't have a mind of their own,

00:02:08.620 --> 00:02:10.890
but by stimulating the fascia

00:02:10.890 --> 00:02:13.300
in a particular location on the body,

00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:16.540
there's a pathway leading
out of that fascia

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:20.430
directly to an organ
called the adrenal medulla,

00:02:20.430 --> 00:02:21.630
I'll explain what all this means,

00:02:21.630 --> 00:02:23.330
that could liberate particular chemicals

00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:26.980
that had a potent
anti-inflammatory effect.

00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:28.430
So what we're basically saying

00:02:28.430 --> 00:02:31.850
is that the nervous system
acts as a set of highways

00:02:31.850 --> 00:02:33.830
between the different
tissues of your body,

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:36.410
calling into action the immune system,

00:02:36.410 --> 00:02:40.170
liberating particular molecules
that can reduce inflammation

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:42.410
and lead to faster healing.

00:02:42.410 --> 00:02:44.430
And I will explain how all of that works

00:02:44.430 --> 00:02:47.700
as well as some other
non-acupuncture methods

00:02:47.700 --> 00:02:50.170
for activating and enhancing the function

00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:51.060
of the immune system.

00:02:51.060 --> 00:02:52.990
