make it that we can't always

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:18.070
go to bed at the same time

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:19.610
and wake up at the exact same time.

00:09:19.610 --> 00:09:21.580
Okay, so we need sleep.

00:09:21.580 --> 00:09:22.720
We do need sunshine.

00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:23.760
Why do we need sunshine?

00:09:23.760 --> 00:09:26.850
Because it sets our rhythm
into a regular state

00:09:26.850 --> 00:09:29.560
where the genes in all of our cells

00:09:29.560 --> 00:09:31.300
can be expressed at the correct times.

00:09:31.300 --> 00:09:33.360
We're sort of a factory
of cells, if you will,

00:09:33.360 --> 00:09:36.240
and that factory can only
run properly if it knows

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:38.020
when certain things should be active

00:09:38.020 --> 00:09:40.310
and when certain cells
should not be active.

00:09:40.310 --> 00:09:42.880
And the best way to coordinate
all of those activities

00:09:42.880 --> 00:09:45.730
of all the cells is to
get sunshine in your eyes

00:09:45.730 --> 00:09:47.980
in the morning and again in the evening,

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:50.200
and not to get too much
bright light in your eyes

00:09:50.200 --> 00:09:51.560
in the middle of the night.

00:09:51.560 --> 00:09:53.900
That's just foundational.

