electroacupuncture to drive

01:50:11.170 --> 01:50:13.130
the vagal adrenal axis."

01:50:13.130 --> 01:50:15.190
And while that's a mouthful,

01:50:15.190 --> 01:50:19.360
now most all of you are probably
familiar with what I mean

01:50:19.360 --> 01:50:21.540
when I say vagal adrenal axis;

01:50:21.540 --> 01:50:23.420
vagal meaning of the vagus,

01:50:23.420 --> 01:50:25.310
and adrenal of the adrenal glands.

01:50:25.310 --> 01:50:27.950
And so perhaps we should not be surprised,

01:50:27.950 --> 01:50:30.250
although excited, nonetheless,

01:50:30.250 --> 01:50:35.250
that when Qiufu's lab looked
at stimulation of the body

01:50:36.660 --> 01:50:38.802
with so-called electroacupuncture.

01:50:38.802 --> 01:50:40.740
So, these are needles where a small bit

01:50:40.740 --> 01:50:43.190
of electrical current, low
level of electrical current,

01:50:43.190 --> 01:50:47.540
is passed into the needle
and therefore into the body.

01:50:47.540 --> 01:50:51.270
They located sites on the
body that can increase

01:50:51.270 --> 01:50:55.140
inflammation by way of releasing
inflammatory cytokines.

01:50:55.140 --> 01:50:57.630
These areas included the abdomen,

01:50:57.630 --> 01:51:01.720
and they found areas on the
body such as the lower limbs,

01:51:01.720 --> 01:51:03.620
or the hind limbs in this case,

01:51:03.620 --> 01:51:07.370
that can stimulate the
vagal adrenal reflex

01:51:07.370 --> 01:51:10.790
and can lead to reduced inflammation.

01:51:10.790 --> 01:51:14.440
And what was really interesting
is that they figured out

01:51:14.440 --> 01:51:17.230
that it was activation of nerve endings

01:51:17.230 --> 01:51:19.120
that resided in the fascia.

01:51:19.120 --> 01:51:20.610
I mentioned earlier what fascia is,

01:51:20.610 --> 01:51:21.460
but just to remind you,

01:51:21.460 --> 01:51:25.210
the fascia is a really
thick sheath of tissue

01:51:25.210 --> 01:51:26.970
that surrounds muscle.

01:51:26.970 --> 01:51:28.581
If ever you've heard of Rolfing,

01:51:28.581 --> 01:51:31.440
Rolfing is a form of very intense massage.

01:51:31.440 --> 01:51:34.560
I've never had this done,
but I've heard about this.

01:51:34.560 --> 01:51:37.070
It involves among other things,

01:51:37.070 --> 01:51:39.580
actually separating the muscle away

01:51:39.580 --> 01:51:40.840
from the fascia somewhat.

01:51:40.840 --> 01:51:43.490
So it's a very, very deep tissue massage.

01:51:43.490 --> 01:51:47.070
Actually a good friend
of mine who had this done

01:51:47.070 --> 01:51:48.410
told me that it was probably

01:51:48.410 --> 01:51:51.880
the most challenging physical experience

01:51:51.880 --> 01:51:53.250
that he had ever been
through going through

01:51:53.250 --> 01:51:54.260
this Rolfing procedure.

01:51:54.260 --> 01:51:57.150
Maybe some of you have have
been Rolfed, as they say,

01:51:57.150 --> 01:51:59.030
and can report to the experience,

01:51:59.030 --> 01:52:00.620
whether or not it was
pleasant or unpleasant,

01:52:00.620 --> 01:52:02.140
or you felt benefits or not.

01:52:02.140 --> 01:52:04.970
In any case, this study
isn't about Rolfing per se,

01:52:04.970 --> 01:52:06.550
but it is about the fascia.

01:52:06.550 --> 01:52:09.280
And so what they discovered
is there's a specific

01:52:09.280 --> 01:52:10.550
population of neurons.

01:52:10.550 --> 01:52:13.170
Those neurons have a name,
as they often do in science.

01:52:13.170 --> 01:52:15.260
Name isn't important, but
if you want to look it up,

01:52:15.260 --> 01:52:20.260
it's the PROKR2 neurons,
P-R-O-K R2 neurons.

01:52:20.490 --> 01:52:23.370
And they send a connection deep into

01:52:23.370 --> 01:52:26.070
the limb fascial tissue, okay?

01:52:26.070 --> 01:52:27.920
And then they send another connection,

01:52:27.920 --> 01:52:30.140
the connections we're
referring to are axons,

01:52:30.140 --> 01:52:30.973
neurons have axons.

01:52:30.973 --> 01:52:34.310
So a wire in one direction that goes

01:52:34.310 --> 01:52:37.850
into the deep fascial
tissue of the lower limb,

01:52:37.850 --> 01:52:39.490
near the calf and thigh.

01:52:39.490 --> 01:52:44.050
And then they send another
wire up into the spinal cord,

01:52:44.050 --> 01:52:47.590
into a region of the hind
brain in the back of your brain

01:52:47.590 --> 01:52:51.170
kind of near your neck
in the medulla oblongata,

01:52:51.170 --> 01:52:53.570
that neuron also has a name
called the DMZ, doesn't matter.

01:52:53.570 --> 01:52:56.840
And that neuron connects
to the adrenal gland

01:52:56.840 --> 01:52:59.160
to release our good old
friends, the catacholamines,

01:52:59.160 --> 01:53:02.830
noradrenaline, adrenaline, and dopamine,

01:53:02.830 --> 01:53:06.340
or norepinephrine,
epinephrin, and dopamine.

01:53:06.340 --> 01:53:11.340
And their release causes a
reduction in inflammation,

01:53:12.120 --> 01:53:14.170
even in response to an
injection of something called

01:53:14.170 --> 01:53:16.400
lipopolysaccharide, which
can actually induce fever.

01:53:16.400 --> 01:53:17.300
So, what does all this saying?

01:53:17.300 --> 01:53:21.490
This is saying that activation
of the deep fascial tissue

01:53:21.490 --> 01:53:26.490
causes a chain of neural
reactions that leads eventually

01:53:26.610 --> 01:53:29.000
to the release of
norepinephrine, noradrenaline,

01:53:29.000 --> 01:53:31.310
adrenaline, and dopamine.

01:53:31.310 --> 01:53:33.480
And once again, lowers inflammation,

01:53:33.480 --> 01:53:35.910
very much like the breathing study

01:53:35.910 --> 01:53:37.650
that we talked about
earlier in the pattern

01:53:37.650 --> 01:53:39.700
of cyclical hyperventilation
with retention,

01:53:39.700 --> 01:53:41.760
leading to reductions in inflammation.

01:53:41.760 --> 01:53:43.360
I can't tell you how happy this makes me.

01:53:43.360 --> 01:53:44.670
I had nothing to do with this work,

01:53:44.670 --> 01:53:47.380
but the reason it makes
me happy is because

01:53:47.380 --> 01:53:51.150
I have a particular
fondness for when practices

01:53:51.150 --> 01:53:53.280
that have existed for many centuries

01:53:53.280 --> 01:53:55.820
or even thousands of
years, such as acupuncture,

01:53:55.820 --> 01:54:00.380
such as respiration work,
start to converge with some

01:54:00.380 --> 01:54:02.770
of the hardcore mechanistic science.

01:54:02.770 --> 01:54:05.780
And the reason this excites
me is not because we want to

01:54:05.780 --> 01:54:08.580
take science and erase the previous tools

01:54:08.580 --> 01:54:11.680
and methods of these ancient
practices, not at all.

01:54:11.680 --> 01:54:13.770
And it certainly isn't
the case that we just want

01:54:13.770 --> 01:54:17.190
to name things or rename
things with modern science.

01:54:17.190 --> 01:54:20.890
What's very exciting is when
we can discover mechanism

01:54:20.890 --> 01:54:23.680
that explains why certain practices work.

01:54:23.680 --> 01:54:28.470
First of all, that validates
those as legitimate practices,

01:54:28.470 --> 01:54:31.270
maybe even insurance
will start to cover them,

01:54:31.270 --> 01:54:33.110
whereas maybe they previously had not,

01:54:33.110 --> 01:54:34.390
I don't know what the current status

01:54:34.390 --> 01:54:36.750
is for insurance coverage of acupuncture.

01:54:36.750 --> 01:54:38.500
I'm guessing there are places that do it,

01:54:38.500 --> 01:54:40.430
maybe others that don't.

01:54:40.430 --> 01:54:43.390
I personally am not somebody
who receives acupuncture.

01:54:43.390 --> 01:54:46.380
I have in the past, but it's
not that I'm in particular

01:54:46.380 --> 01:54:48.770
a fan of it, but I think that
there are a number of people

01:54:48.770 --> 01:54:49.790
that have benefited from it.

01:54:49.790 --> 01:54:51.640
So, I think that's wonderful.

01:54:51.640 --> 01:54:54.280
Breath work and respiration
work is something

01:54:54.280 --> 01:54:56.440
that I've cultivated as a
practice over the years.

01:54:56.440 --> 01:54:58.910
I mentioned earlier, how
I use it to push back

01:54:58.910 --> 01:55:00.760
