01:55:00.760 --> 01:55:04.050
And now that doesn't sound like total...

01:55:04.050 --> 01:55:06.010
You know, like just a
figment of my imagination,

01:55:06.010 --> 01:55:06.970
there's actually a mechanism,

01:55:06.970 --> 01:55:09.140
a published mechanism to explain it.

01:55:09.140 --> 01:55:11.640
But the most exciting
thing to me about all this

01:55:11.640 --> 01:55:15.120
is that practices that
traditionally have been shrouded

01:55:15.120 --> 01:55:17.520
in complicated language
or were the unique domain

01:55:17.520 --> 01:55:21.210
of the practitioners and relied on phrases

01:55:21.210 --> 01:55:23.870
like the meridians or the chakras,

01:55:23.870 --> 01:55:25.860
of which I think is
perfectly valid language,

01:55:25.860 --> 01:55:27.350
but doesn't inform mechanism.

01:55:27.350 --> 01:55:31.190
And then in a separate community,
the community I come from,

01:55:31.190 --> 01:55:32.440
the community of scientists,

01:55:32.440 --> 01:55:35.960
have used language like PROKR2 neurons,

01:55:35.960 --> 01:55:38.340
medulla oblongata, vagal adrenal axis.

01:55:38.340 --> 01:55:40.760
And basically no one can
communicate with one another

01:55:40.760 --> 01:55:41.990
because the language is shrouding.

01:55:41.990 --> 01:55:46.590
What we're now starting to see
is that at their convergence

01:55:46.590 --> 01:55:48.160
is a common mechanism.

01:55:48.160 --> 01:55:49.670
And with that understanding,

01:55:49.670 --> 01:55:52.490
what's going to be really terrific

01:55:52.490 --> 01:55:55.100
is as new protocols start to emerge.

01:55:55.100 --> 01:55:57.390
So in understanding
mechanisms and pathways,

01:55:57.390 --> 01:56:01.360
and in being able to understand
the base set of practices

01:56:01.360 --> 01:56:04.160
like breathing, like
electroacupuncture, and so forth,

01:56:04.160 --> 01:56:08.030
we can now start to daydream
in a very realistic way

01:56:08.030 --> 01:56:10.330
